# QA Report — Sprint M4a
# Adversarial Spec Review (Sonnet R9)
# Date: 2026-05-03

---

## [FAIL] HIGH — `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` budget formula not updated (DK-6 parity break)

**What the spec says:** A2b fixes `firstSlideBudget` in `splitAgendaIntoSlides` (instagram-post.ts) and `buildManualSlides` (instagram-overrides.ts): `hasGrid ? SLIDE_BUDGET : SLIDE1_BUDGET` — no more `leadHeightPx(lead)` reduction.

**What a developer will implement:** Only the two functions listed in Files-to-Change. `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` (same file, lines 682–712) is not in the spec at all.

**Bug that results:** `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` keeps its old formula:
```ts
const firstSlideBudget = hasGrid && lead
  ? Math.max(SLIDE_BUDGET - leadHeightPx(lead), 200)
  : (hasGrid ? SLIDE_BUDGET : SLIDE1_BUDGET);
```
The LayoutEditor calls this function to project slide boundaries for the auto-mode preview. After M4a, the renderer uses full `SLIDE_BUDGET` for the first text-slide when `hasGrid`, but the editor still uses the reduced `SLIDE_BUDGET - leadHeightPx(lead)` budget. Editor and renderer diverge — the editor shows fewer blocks on Slide 2 than the renderer actually places there. This directly violates the DK-6 editor/renderer boundary parity guarantee (the property test in E2b verifies renderer correctness but never tests `projectAutoBlocksToSlides`).

**Second consequence:** `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` also has its own grid-alone-guard (lines 709–711):
```ts
if (compactedGroups.length === 0 && hasGrid && lead) {
  compactedGroups = [...compactedGroups, [] as ExportBlock[]];
}
```
This guard mirrors the one in `splitAgendaIntoSlides` (see separate finding below). It needs the same fix — but is not mentioned.

**Third consequence:** `leadHeightPx` is still called by `projectAutoBlocksToSlides`. The spec's Files-to-Change item (f) tells the implementer to "grep `leadHeightPx` ob noch andere Aufrufer in der Datei existieren" — the grep WILL find `projectAutoBlocksToSlides`. The disposition says to keep the function if callers remain. So `leadHeightPx` stays. But the real issue (diverging budget) is left unfixed.

**Codex will catch this as a P1**: "A2b removes `leadHeightPx`-based budget reduction from two functions but the third instance in `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` remains."

**Fix needed in spec:** Add `projectAutoBlocksToSlides` to Files-to-Change for `instagram-post.ts` with: same budget fix (`hasGrid ? SLIDE_BUDGET : SLIDE1_BUDGET`), same grid-alone-guard removal, and verify `leadHeightPx` is truly unused after all three fixes.

