## [FAIL] HIGH — TypeScript error: `slide.gridImages.map()` without null-guard in cover-branch (A4b)

**What the spec says (A4b code snippet):**
```ts
if (slide.kind === "grid" && slide.isFirst) {
  const gridSpec = computeSlide1GridSpec(slide.gridImages ?? [], (slide.gridImages ?? []).length);
  return (
    <ImageGrid
      cols={gridSpec.columns}
      images={gridSpec.cells}
      dataUrls={gridImageDataUrls ?? slide.gridImages.map(() => null)}  // ← here
      maxHeight={GRID_MAX_HEIGHT_COVER}
    />
  );
}
```

**What a developer will implement:** Exactly this code. `slide.gridImages` is typed as `GridImage[] | undefined` on the flat `Slide` type (no discriminated union — `kind === "grid"` narrowing does NOT narrow `gridImages` to non-optional). TypeScript strict mode raises `Object is possibly 'undefined'.ts(2532)` on `.map()`.

**Bug that results:** `pnpm exec tsc --noEmit` fails. Code Quality Gate is violated before any tests can run.

Note: the pure-image-slide branch handles this correctly with an explicit throw-guard before accessing `slide.gridImages`, which gives TypeScript flow-narrowing. The cover-branch has no equivalent guard.

**Fix needed in spec:** Change the dataUrls fallback to:
```ts
dataUrls={gridImageDataUrls ?? (slide.gridImages ?? []).map(() => null)}
```
Or introduce a local: `const safeGridImages = slide.gridImages ?? [];` before the `computeSlide1GridSpec` call and use it in both places.

