## [FAIL] HIGH — Grid-alone-guard creates blank trailing slide for hasGrid + lead + empty-body items

**What the spec says:** A2b removes the Lead-height reduction from Slide-2 budget. Lead moves to the grid-cover slide (A2). The grid-path `slidesWithChunks.forEach` sets `leadOnSlide: false` for all text-slides (A3b).

**What a developer will implement:** The spec does not mention the grid-alone-guard at lines 453–455 of `splitAgendaIntoSlides`:
```ts
if (compactedGroups.length === 0 && hasGrid && lead) {
  compactedGroups = [...compactedGroups, [] as ExportBlock[]];
}
```

**Bug that results:** When an Agenda item has images (hasGrid) + a lead + zero body-content blocks:

- Pre-M4a: guard adds `[]` group → forEach creates text-slide with `leadOnSlide: i === 0 && Boolean(lead) = true` → Lead renders on Slide 2. Correct.
- Post-M4a: guard still fires → forEach creates text-slide with `leadOnSlide: false` (A3b NACHHER) → no Lead → empty body → **a blank slide** (just HeaderRow + empty body-div) appended after the grid-cover. Regression.

The correct fix is to remove or condition the guard: after M4a, Lead lives on the grid-cover slide, so there is no need for an empty text-slide when body is empty.

**No E2 test covers this case:** The spec's E2 slide-count / budget tests use items with substantial body content. Zero-body items with grid + lead are never exercised. The regression goes undetected until E5 visual smoke (if the tester happens to use such an item).

**Fix needed in spec:** Add to instagram-post.ts Files-to-Change: "Remove the grid-alone-guard (`if (compactedGroups.length === 0 && hasGrid && lead) ...`) in `splitAgendaIntoSlides` — the guard was solely for carrying Lead on a text-slide; Lead now lives on the grid-cover." And add a matching E2 unit test: `splitAgendaIntoSlides` with `hasGrid=true`, non-empty lead, empty body → slides = exactly 1 slide (`kind: "grid"`).

